His "therapy" actively harms people. It's irresponsible to claim something is therapy, pretend it does people good, and when pressed claim it only does a tiny minority some sort of harm. If people want to lead a spiritually celibate lifestyle, they wouldn't go to him at all. They would lead a spiritually celibate lifestyle.